# Foster Construction Website Replacement Plan

This document outlines the evaluation of the existing `fosterconstructionga.com` website and provides a detailed, step-by-step technical plan for building a modern, high-performance, and visually superior replacement. This plan is formatted so that it can be directly imported or fed into Claude Code.

## 1. Evaluation of Existing Website

### Visual & Aesthetic Profile
*   **Palette:** Deep navy blue (`#00214d`), crisp white, and light gray accents.
*   **Typography:** Clean, sans-serif fonts (like Inter/Roboto) for a professional, trustworthy construction brand feel.
*   **Imagery:** Hero sections with dark overlays, prominent high-resolution galleries of past work (kitchens, bathrooms, additions).

### Desktop Components
*   **Sticky Header:** Logo left, navigation center (Services, Galleries dropdowns), and dual CTA buttons right ("Send us a Text", "Call Now").
*   **Hero Section:** Full-width background image with overlay, bold H1 value proposition, and a "Book a Consultation" primary CTA.
*   **Service Grid:** Interactive cards detailing specialty services.
*   **Social Proof:** Google/Facebook review badges and a testimonial carousel.
*   **Footer:** Multi-column layout with business hours, service areas (Marietta, GA), and quick links.

### Mobile Components
*   **Navigation:** Responsive hamburger menu that cleanly tucks away desktop links.
*   **Layout:** Grid items (services, reviews) stack vertically.
*   **Floating CTA:** A persistent "Send us a Text" button stays fixed at the bottom right corner for immediate lead capture on mobile devices.

